by its military-intelligence complex. china and india went to war in 1962 over a border dispute. though current relations are peaceful, there is still military rivalry and no land crossings are allowed between the two countries, though one border crossing between sikkim and tibet was re-opened in 2006 for trade (but not tourists). security concerns over pakistan and china prompted india to test nuclear weapons twice (including the 1974 tests described as "peaceful explosions"). india wants to be accepted as a legitimate nuclear power and is campaigning for a permanent security council seat. india is proud of its democratic record. 